rks%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long-standing%20arrangement%20that%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lost-weirdest-wartime-income-streams-gas-pipeline-ukraine-deal-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%20as%20a%20conduit%20for%20westbound%20Russian%20gas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20agreement%20that%20continued%20even%20as%20full-scale%20war%20broke%20out%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEuropean%20countries%20that%20received%20that%20gas%2C%20such%20as%20Slovakia%20and%20Austria%2C%20were%20paying%20Russia%20for%20this%20energy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Fwhat-happens-when-russian-gas-europe-via-ukraine-stops-2024-12-23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%20calculated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%20that%20the%20Russian%20economy%20would%20earn%20about%20%245%20billion%20in%202024%20alone%20from%20piping%20gas%20through%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20news%20agency%20estimated%20that%20Kyiv%20stood%20to%20receive%20between%20%24800%20million%20to%20%241%20billion%20over%20that%20year%20from%20collecting%20transit%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20signaled%20for%20months%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20let%20the%20deal%20expire%20on%20January%201%2C%202025%2C%20and%20it's%20now%20made%20good%20on%20that%20pledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Putin%20was%20presented%20with%20the%20Russian%20presidency%20more%20than%2025%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20annual%20gas%20transit%20through%20Ukraine%20to%20Europe%20totaled%20more%20than%20130%20billion%20cubic%20meters.%20Today%2C%20it%20equals%200%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Ukrainian%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FZelenskyyUa%2Fstatus%2F1874481379326488916%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVolodymyr%20Zelenskyy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20energy%20minister%2C%20Herman%20Halushchenko%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmev.gov.ua%2Fnovyna%2Ftranzyt-rosiy